description:
&lt;p&gt;A fantastic opportunity have arisen in Southend Hospital to join an organisation with a reputation for excellence in the way it cares for the people it serves. We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Pharmacy Assistant to join the Pharmacy department!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Pharmacy Technical Services Unit comprises the Sterile Production Unit, Pre-pack unit, Radiopharmacy and Cytotoxic unit. Supervised by the senior technician in charge, the post holder will provide support services to the Pharmacy Technical Services department, including the ordering, receipt, storage and supply of Pharmaceuticals and other stocks, the manufacture of aseptic products in both the aseptic and cytotoxic unit and the pre-packing of medication in the pre-pack unit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This person will also assist senior staff with support duties essential to the smooth functioning on the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;15 hours per week 1 position&lt;br /&gt;The hours are: Monday to Friday 9am to 5:30pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be some extra hours before and after Bank Holidays.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At Southend Hospital NHS Trust we strongly believe in patient care and want to attract likeminded people to help build and maintain a supportive and enjoyable place to work, that’s why our trust values are ‘Everybody Matters, Everything Counts and Everyone is Responsible’&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSue GissingJob titleChief Pharmacy Technician Technical ServicesEmail addresssue.gissing@southend.nhs.ukTelephone number01702 385338&lt;/p&gt;
